Public API Contracts (Astro ↔ Java) – Locked Specification

Scope

This document locks the public (unauthenticated) API contracts consumed by the storefront (Astro + islands) for:
	•	Site content (via Java → Payload gateway)
	•	Store catalog (products, categories, images, linked products)
	•	Checkout order creation (offline-first)
	•	Payment initiation (Wompi later, optional in MVP)

This spec follows the locked API Design Conventions:
	•	Base: /api/public/v1/...
	•	Offset pagination: page, pageSize, response { data, page, pageSize, total }
	•	Filtering via query params, q for search, sort=field:dir
	•	RFC7807-like errors with traceId
	•	Enums UPPER_SNAKE_CASE, timestamps ISO-8601 UTC

⸻

1) Tenant Resolution (Locked)

1.1 Primary (production): Host-based
	•	Tenant is resolved from HTTP Host header.
	•	Supports custom domains.

1.2 Fallback (development / diagnostics): tenantSlug path
	•	Alternate endpoints exist under:
	•	/api/public/v1/tenants/{tenantSlug}/...

1.3 Behavior when tenant cannot be resolved
	•	Return 404 with problem response:
	•	type: .../tenant-not-found

