3) Public Catalog APIs (Store module)

3.1 List categories

GET /api/public/v1/catalog/categories

Query params:
	•	status (optional, default ACTIVE)

Response:

{
  "data": [
    { "id": "uuid", "name": "Makeup", "slug": "makeup", "sortOrder": 10 }
  ],
  "page": 1,
  "pageSize": 100,
  "total": 1
}

Notes:
	•	For categories, server may ignore pagination and always return all ACTIVE categories (still wrapped).

⸻

3.2 List products

GET /api/public/v1/catalog/products

Query params (all optional):
	•	page (default 1)
	•	pageSize (default 20, max 100)
	•	status (default ACTIVE)
	•	primaryCategoryId (UUID)
	•	categoryId (UUID) — matches additional categories too
	•	q (search)
	•	sort allowlist:
	•	createdAt:desc|asc
	•	priceCents:asc|desc
	•	name:asc|desc

Response (example):

{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "uuid",
      "name": "Lipstick – Red",
      "slug": "lipstick-red",
      "shortDescription": "...",
      "priceCents": 45000,
      "currency": "COP",
      "primaryImageUrl": "https://...",
      "primaryCategory": { "id": "uuid", "slug": "makeup", "name": "Makeup" },
      "badges": ["NEW"]
    }
  ],
  "page": 1,
  "pageSize": 20,
  "total": 182
}


