4) Public Checkout APIs (Orders module)

4.1 Checkout model (Locked MVP behavior)
	•	Storefront maintains the cart client-side.
	•	Public API creates an order from a cart payload.
	•	Order starts in:
	•	fulfillmentStatus = NEW
	•	paymentStatus = UNPAID or PENDING depending on method
	•	Merchant must confirm later in Merchant Admin.

4.2 Create order (checkout)

POST /api/public/v1/checkout/orders

Request (example):

{
  "customer": {
    "name": "Ana",
    "phone": "+57...",
    "email": "ana@email.com"
  },
  "fulfillment": {
    "type": "DELIVERY",
    "deliveryAddress": {
      "line1": "Calle 123",
      "line2": "Apt 4",
      "city": "Bogotá",
      "notes": "Call on arrival"
    }
  },
  "payment": {
    "method": "NEQUI"
  },
  "items": [
    { "productId": "uuid", "quantity": 2 }
  ]
}

Server responsibilities:
	•	Validate products are ACTIVE and belong to tenant
	•	Price is calculated server-side using current priceCents
	•	Store snapshots into order_items
	•	Create order with:
	•	fulfillmentStatus = NEW
	•	paymentStatus = PENDING for offline methods

Response:

{
  "orderId": "uuid",
  "orderNumber": "ORD-000123",
  "currency": "COP",
  "subtotalCents": 90000,
  "totalCents": 90000,
  "payment": {
    "method": "NEQUI",
    "status": "PENDING",
    "instructions": {
      "title": "Pay with Nequi",
      "details": ["Send 90.000 COP to +57...", "Use reference ORD-000123"],
      "reference": "ORD-000123"
    }
  },
  "fulfillment": {
    "type": "DELIVERY",
    "status": "NEW"
  },
  "createdAt": "2026-01-29T00:00:00Z"
}

Errors:
	•	400 validation errors (missing phone, invalid productId)
	•	409 out-of-stock can be added later; MVP may skip strict stock enforcement

