5) Optional: Payment initiation (Wompi)

Wompi is supported via the payment provider abstraction and webhooks (not public).
If enabled for a tenant, the storefront can initiate a payment session.

5.1 Create a payment attempt for an order

POST /api/public/v1/checkout/orders/{orderId}/payments

Request:

{
  "provider": "WOMPI",
  "returnUrl": "https://{tenantDomain}/checkout/complete"
}

Response (example):

{
  "paymentAttemptId": "uuid",
  "provider": "WOMPI",
  "status": "PENDING",
  "clientParams": {
    "publicKey": "...",
    "amountInCents": 90000,
    "currency": "COP",
    "reference": "ORD-000123",
    "signature": "..."
  }
}

Notes:
	•	Provider confirmation is webhook-driven (not public endpoints).

⸻

6) Rate Limiting (Locked)

Public checkout endpoints must be rate limited:
	•	/api/public/v1/checkout/orders
	•	/api/public/v1/checkout/orders/*/payments

Default thresholds (from Observability spec):
	•	Per IP: 10 checkout attempts / 1 minute
	•	Per tenant: 100 checkout attempts / 10 minutes

Return 429 with Retry-After and include traceId.

⸻

7) Fallback Endpoints (tenantSlug)

The following endpoints must exist for dev/fallback:
	•	GET /api/public/v1/tenants/{tenantSlug}/site/settings
	•	GET /api/public/v1/tenants/{tenantSlug}/site/pages/{pageType}
	•	GET /api/public/v1/tenants/{tenantSlug}/catalog/categories
	•	GET /api/public/v1/tenants/{tenantSlug}/catalog/products
	•	GET /api/public/v1/tenants/{tenantSlug}/catalog/products/{slug}
	•	POST /api/public/v1/tenants/{tenantSlug}/checkout/orders

Behavior matches Host-based endpoints.

⸻

8) Final Locked Summary
	•	Public APIs live under /api/public/v1/...
	•	Tenant is resolved by Host header (primary) with tenantSlug fallback endpoints
	•	Public content is served via Java gateway to Payload
	•	Public catalog includes products, categories, images, and linked products
	•	Checkout creates orders from client-side cart and returns offline instructions
	•	Optional Wompi payment attempt initiation exists (provider confirmation via webhooks)
	•	Rate limiting enforced on checkout endpoints

This specification is locked and implementation-ready.